{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"59f522",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Inhaled short-acting anticholinergic agents (ipratropium)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f602f0",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Dry mouth, mydriasis on contact with eye, tachycardia, tremors; rarely acute narrow-angle glaucoma; this drug class has been shown to be safe in a wide range of doses and clinical settings"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"940997",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Generally used as needed for mild disease with few symptoms; avoid using both short- and long-acting anticholinergics"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
